00:21:57,396 --> 00:22:00,229
So I grabbed Kylian by the collar,
and I told him,

267
00:22:00,312 --> 00:22:02,646
"Yo, what you got on you?"

268
00:22:02,729 --> 00:22:03,771
"Gimme your money."

269
00:22:04,771 --> 00:22:06,896
He looked me in the eyes,

270
00:22:06,979 --> 00:22:08,521
and said to me calmly…

271
00:22:09,646 --> 00:22:10,896
"I have none on me."

272
00:22:10,979 --> 00:22:13,521
"But if you're needing a job…
we should talk."

273
00:22:13,604 --> 00:22:14,479
What?

274
00:22:15,521 --> 00:22:16,979
Come on, for real?

275
00:22:18,646 --> 00:22:22,812
It was beyond what he said or…
how he said it.

276
00:22:22,896 --> 00:22:24,896
[gentle music continues]

277
00:22:25,687 --> 00:22:26,979
It was his look.

278
00:22:28,021 --> 00:22:30,437
- What happened? After that?
- [phone vibrating]

279
00:22:30,521 --> 00:22:32,062
[music stops]

280
00:22:34,146 --> 00:22:35,437
To be continued.

281
00:22:36,521 --> 00:22:37,521
Who this?

282
00:22:41,396 --> 00:22:42,812
Yo, Xhésus.

283
00:22:44,187 --> 00:22:45,937
[whispers] Give me the phone after you.

284
00:22:46,562 --> 00:22:48,854
Yeah, all clear. We made it safely.

285
00:22:48,937 --> 00:22:50,937
- We're waiting for you.
- Could you pass me that?

286
00:22:51,021 --> 00:22:52,729
[snapping]

287
00:22:53,979 --> 00:22:55,354
At 2:00 p.m.

288
00:22:55,437 --> 00:22:57,271
Okay. Okay.

289
00:22:57,771 --> 00:23:00,187
- Could you hand me the phone?
- [line disconnects]

290
00:23:00,271 --> 00:23:03,354
You seriously hung up?
I said pass me the phone!

291
00:23:03,437 --> 00:23:04,604
What's your problem?

292
00:23:05,187 --> 00:23:06,229
Damn it!

293
00:23:09,854 --> 00:23:10,854
[line ringing]

294
00:23:12,687 --> 00:23:15,729
- [automated voice] Your call has been--
- Fuck! I'm gonna kill him!

295
00:23:18,729 --> 00:23:19,562
[exhales]

296
00:23:19,646 --> 00:23:23,271
DUCOS PENITENTIARY

297
00:23:23,354 --> 00:23:26,896
- [dark music playing]
- [door buzzing]

298
00:23:47,562 --> 00:23:49,437
[Fabrice] Aren't you gonna sit down?

299
00:23:52,604 --> 00:23:54,646
What happened? Are you sick?

300
00:24:05,646 --> 00:24:07,479
[exhales weakly]

301
00:24:10,812 --> 00:24:13,104
- [Fabrice] No way, brother.
- [crying softly]

302
00:24:21,437 --> 00:24:24,479
We'll make him pay. I promise.

303
00:24:26,229 --> 00:24:30,104
I'll take the kids in gladly.
But for the two eldest, I have no space.

304
00:24:30,187 --> 00:24:32,896
Auntie, cut the bullshit.
The floor is half empty.

305
00:24:33,562 --> 00:24:35,396
Okay, children,
hop up to each of your rooms.

306
00:24:35,479 --> 00:24:37,187
I prepared the beds.

307
00:24:39,354 --> 00:24:40,437
Head up.

308
00:24:40,521 --> 00:24:41,521
Here.

309
00:24:47,271 --> 00:24:48,271
Régine…

310
00:24:48,771 --> 00:24:50,937
they'll place Cass and Léo with strangers.

311
00:24:51,021 --> 00:24:54,771
I'm also a stranger, apparently.
You made that clear to me.

312
00:24:54,854 --> 00:24:56,854
That one, he broke my arm.

313
00:24:56,937 --> 00:25:01,271
And that one there, he insulted me.
Do you take me for an idiot?

314
00:25:03,229 --> 00:25:04,229
Wait.

315
00:25:05,187 --> 00:25:06,562
Try to understand.

316
00:25:07,187 --> 00:25:09,187
We lost our minds with the grief.

317
00:25:09,271 --> 00:25:10,479
The children especially.

318
00:25:11,104 --> 00:25:12,646
It was hard being separated.

319
00:25:17,021 --> 00:25:18,646
As an apology, Auntie.

320
00:25:19,729 --> 00:25:20,854
This is for this week.

321
00:25:20,937 --> 00:25:23,271
I'll bring the same for next week
and the one after that.

322
00:25:27,896 --> 00:25:28,896
[sucks teeth]

323
00:25:29,854 --> 00:25:32,854
[bittersweet music playing]

324
00:26:11,937 --> 00:26:15,729
The streets, brother.
We gotta work them too, to our advantage.

325
00:26:25,396 --> 00:26:27,396
[music fading]

326
00:26:30,604 --> 00:26:32,729
[Léo] Uncle, can we talk for a minute?

327
00:26:33,854 --> 00:26:35,187
About what?

328
00:26:35,687 --> 00:26:37,937
It's, um, a bit, um…

329
00:26:39,812 --> 00:26:41,354
What? Don't be shy.

330
00:26:43,104 --> 00:26:44,104
What is it?

331
00:26:44,604 --> 00:26:46,979
Kylian told me
to tell you that you gotta take a trip.

332
00:26:48,229 --> 00:26:49,521
Wherever you want.

333
00:26:49,604 --> 00:26:53,312
[chuckles] Yeah, okay. I'll be in Miami.
Are you paying my ticket?

334
00:26:54,521 --> 00:26:57,354
You're leaving tonight
and coming back when we say so.

335
00:27:00,187 --> 00:27:02,687
Huh. You're all completely insane.

336
00:27:03,312 --> 00:27:06,479
Get out before daylight
or your face will have a huge hole.

337
00:27:06,562 --> 00:27:08,646
Or I might even kill you.

338
00:27:15,646 --> 00:27:17,646
[insects chirping in background]

339
00:27:26,146 --> 00:27:27,229
[floorboard creaks]

340
00:27:35,979 --> 00:27:37,146
It wasn't me.

341
00:27:38,812 --> 00:27:39,812
[groggily] What?

342
00:27:40,646 --> 00:27:42,354
The fire wasn't me.

343
00:27:42,437 --> 00:27:43,646
I would never do that.

344
00:27:51,396 --> 00:27:53,021
What do you want, Nat?

345
00:27:54,604 --> 00:27:56,146
There's nothing to steal here.

346
00:27:58,854 --> 00:28:00,854
[angrily] Brother, I'm not a thief!
Listen to me!

347
00:28:05,187 --> 00:28:07,604
I can't fucking believe this.
This is crazy.

348
00:28:12,021 --> 00:28:14,437
[Kingsley] Yo! What are you looking for?

349
00:28:14,521 --> 00:28:16,354
- What are you looking for?
- Bro, my ring!

350
00:28:16,979 --> 00:28:19,771
I don't want it to burn
like the rest of the house!

351
00:28:23,437 --> 00:28:26,271
[muttering] Besides,
that's all I have left of her.

352
00:28:26,354 --> 00:28:28,937
[crying softly]
That's all I have left of her.

353
00:28:34,937 --> 00:28:37,146
It's in mom's jewelry box, man.

354
00:28:38,604 --> 00:28:39,979
Marv has it.

355
00:28:50,604 --> 00:28:53,604
["Selling Dope 2" by Evil P playing]

356
00:28:59,354 --> 00:29:02,354
["Selling Dope 2" continues playing]

357
00:29:08,521 --> 00:29:10,646
Wow! Thanks a lot. My guys.

358
00:29:10,729 --> 00:29:12,937
Thanks? It's our job, bro.

359
00:29:13,021 --> 00:29:14,562
Why are you thanking us?

360
00:29:15,062 --> 00:29:17,187
Yeah, but I mean, thank you for your work.

361
00:29:17,271 --> 00:29:18,354
No problem.

362
00:29:27,437 --> 00:29:30,271
Would y'all be interested
in a job for a few extra hours?

363
00:29:30,354 --> 00:29:31,396
It pays very well.

364
00:29:35,771 --> 00:29:37,771
[song fading]

365
00:29:41,354 --> 00:29:42,771
[knock on door]

366
00:29:58,687 --> 00:30:00,354
I'm here for the birthday.

367
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,479
Keep it open.

368
00:30:15,562 --> 00:30:17,396
We're waiting on someone else.

369
00:30:18,271 --> 00:30:19,562
Did all go as planned?

370
00:30:20,062 --> 00:30:21,229
As you can see.

371
00:30:21,729 --> 00:30:23,021
Perfect.

372
00:30:23,104 --> 00:30:25,021
My guys are on site waiting for info.

373
00:30:27,229 --> 00:30:28,604
The sample.

374
00:30:53,104 --> 00:30:54,437
It checks out.

375
00:30:56,062 --> 00:30:57,854
- [light knock on door]
- We're good.

376
00:31:09,312 --> 00:31:12,312
[suspenseful music playing]

377
00:31:27,604 --> 00:31:30,646
- I told you to stay in the room.
- Yes, I know. I heard.

378
00:31:31,146 --> 00:31:31,979
Gentlemen.

379
00:31:35,646 --> 00:31:36,646
Leave, we're good.

380
00:31:41,104 --> 00:31:43,354
[Annabelle] Continue.
Don't mind me. Go ahead.

381
00:31:47,396 --> 00:31:49,479
The payment will be done by installments.

382
00:31:49,562 --> 00:31:51,562
First two will be done today.

383
00:31:51,646 --> 00:31:54,271
Twenty-four crypto accounts
will be credited.

384
00:31:54,354 --> 00:31:57,104
The key will be shared privately
by email with Milord.

385
00:31:57,604 --> 00:31:59,604
Another payment will be made in cash,

386
00:31:59,687 --> 00:32:02,146
which corresponds
to about 8% of the total.

387
00:32:02,229 --> 00:32:04,146
The rest will be paid in cannabis.

388
00:32:04,229 --> 00:32:06,479
Our shipment is en route to Mada.

389
00:32:06,979 --> 00:32:08,187
So 20 kilos are for you.

390
00:32:09,521 --> 00:32:13,104
In case of loss of cargo, you'll receive
the equivalent in crypto within 48 hours.

391
00:32:14,437 --> 00:32:15,812
How can we be sure of that?

392
00:32:17,104 --> 00:32:19,396
I'm taking 70% percent as my commission.

393
00:32:21,812 --> 00:32:26,062
It's all here in detail in the group
on Telegram about this transaction.

394
00:32:28,271 --> 00:32:30,937
The total is 2.3 million in euros.

395
00:32:31,771 --> 00:32:34,437
Minus my commission,
that makes two million for you.

396
00:32:36,812 --> 00:32:38,437
We're just missing…

397
00:32:39,187 --> 00:32:41,187
the locker number for this.

398
00:32:42,687 --> 00:32:43,812
And the code.

399
00:32:44,437 --> 00:32:47,062
[suspenseful music continues]

400
00:32:58,521 --> 00:32:59,729
[text message whooshes]

401
00:33:04,687 --> 00:33:06,062
[sighs]

402
00:33:09,146 --> 00:33:11,146
[phone vibrating]

403
00:33:18,729 --> 00:33:19,771
Yes?

404
00:33:23,479 --> 00:33:24,562
Yeah.

405
00:33:27,312 --> 00:33:28,396
Okay.

406
00:33:30,312 --> 00:33:31,437
We're good.

407
00:33:32,646 --> 00:33:34,104
No, there's a problem.

408
00:33:35,812 --> 00:33:37,021
A problem?

409
00:33:38,354 --> 00:33:39,771
Just something to settle.

410
00:33:39,854 --> 00:33:42,979
Xhésus? Can I talk to you real quick?

411
00:33:43,062 --> 00:33:46,687
- I can hear you.
- [laughs dryly] No. This way, please.

412
00:33:48,229 --> 00:33:51,479
[suspenseful music continues]

413
00:33:55,812 --> 00:33:57,104
[door slams]

414
00:33:57,646 --> 00:33:59,979
[shouts] What's your problem?
We fuck, then you ghost me?

415
00:34:00,062 --> 00:34:01,979
- [softly] Lower your voice.
- If I feel like it!

416
00:34:02,062 --> 00:34:04,271
Am I a sex doll, is that it?

417
00:34:04,354 --> 00:34:06,479
You know, I see when you read my messages.

418
00:34:06,562 --> 00:34:09,896
[faintly] Don't roll your eyes at me
or I swear I'll beat the shit out of you.

419
00:34:10,396 --> 00:34:13,104
- Like I give a shit. I would do anything.
- [door locks]

420
00:34:13,187 --> 00:34:14,271
Yo!

421
00:34:14,354 --> 00:34:16,604
- What's happening there?
- What do I know?

422
00:34:17,104 --> 00:34:20,312
Do you know the men out there? Trust me,
you don't want to fuck with them.

423
00:34:20,396 --> 00:34:23,396
- [sucks teeth]
- [tensely] Hey man, what are you doing?

424
00:34:23,479 --> 00:34:24,854
Calling the purity police.

425
00:34:26,187 --> 00:34:27,229
I'm kidding.

426
00:34:27,312 --> 00:34:29,979
[Annabelle faintly] This is the time
to make trouble, sweetheart.

427
00:34:30,062 --> 00:34:32,021
Xhésus! Everything okay?

428
00:34:32,104 --> 00:34:34,312
You're completely insane.
What's with you? Let me out!

429
00:34:34,396 --> 00:34:35,437
You're not leaving.

430
00:34:35,521 --> 00:34:38,521
[suspenseful music continues]

431
00:34:39,854 --> 00:34:41,021
[sighs]

432
00:34:44,604 --> 00:34:46,604
[music fades]

433
00:34:52,646 --> 00:34:53,646
Hi.

434
00:34:55,271 --> 00:34:56,271
Hello.

435
00:34:58,104 --> 00:34:59,729
Are you still at the boarding school?

436
00:35:00,562 --> 00:35:01,562
Yes.

437
00:35:06,021 --> 00:35:07,979
You could've messaged me, all the same.

438
00:35:09,021 --> 00:35:10,021
I mean…

439
00:35:17,187 --> 00:35:19,271
You got nothing? Super.

440
00:35:19,354 --> 00:35:20,479
Your uncle.

441
00:35:22,021 --> 00:35:24,104
He made it clear
he doesn't want us to be together.

442
00:35:24,187 --> 00:35:27,396
What? What did he say to you, exactly?

443
00:35:27,479 --> 00:35:30,437
He said that I'm a bad match
for you, your family.

444
00:35:30,521 --> 00:35:32,312
That I'm not welcome, among other things.

445
00:35:32,396 --> 00:35:35,021
That fucking dumbass racist! Pathetic!

446
00:35:36,437 --> 00:35:38,687
Is it even possible to be such an ass?

447
00:35:45,687 --> 00:35:47,229
You should've told me.

448
00:35:49,354 --> 00:35:51,354
[phone ringing]

449
00:35:54,771 --> 00:35:56,312
- I gotta take it. I'm sorry.
- Come on.

450
00:35:59,229 --> 00:36:00,062
What?

451
00:36:00,146 --> 00:36:03,437
[Fatso] Your sister's being a pain
in the ass. She's gonna ruin everything.

452
00:36:03,521 --> 00:36:05,937
A simple "yes, no, leave me alone"
would've sufficed.

453
00:36:06,521 --> 00:36:07,896
What the fuck do you want?

454
00:36:08,812 --> 00:36:10,062
One, an apology.

455
00:36:10,562 --> 00:36:13,104
- Two, an explanation.
- [phone ringing]

456
00:36:20,396 --> 00:36:21,604
Then we'll see.

457
00:36:22,187 --> 00:36:24,479
Fuck! She's a pain, bro!

458
00:36:24,562 --> 00:36:27,271
- A family of clowns. My life's a circus.
- [phone beeps]

459
00:36:30,771 --> 00:36:32,771
[phone vibrating]

460
00:36:33,729 --> 00:36:36,354
You know what?
This is pissing me the fuck off, bro.

461
00:36:36,437 --> 00:36:38,354
- [bangs]
- [phone vibrating]

462
00:36:38,979 --> 00:36:41,562
- They're screwing us over! Take the bag!
- [vibrating continues]

463
00:36:41,646 --> 00:36:43,979
- You better stay put.
- Are you fucking crazy, bro?

464
00:36:44,687 --> 00:36:48,146
- You don't want to mess with me, fucker!
- [vibrating continues]

465
00:36:52,229 --> 00:36:54,146
All good. We're cool.

466
00:36:56,937 --> 00:36:58,062
We are good.

467
00:37:03,979 --> 00:37:05,312
Something wrong?

468
00:37:06,979 --> 00:37:08,021
I'm sorry, Lily.

469
00:37:08,104 --> 00:37:09,771
My life is bizarre.

470
00:37:09,854 --> 00:37:12,521
Maybe your uncle has a point.
It's pointless.

471
00:37:12,604 --> 00:37:14,854
Tell me what's happening. Let me in.

472
00:37:17,437 --> 00:37:18,437
Forget it.

473
00:37:25,479 --> 00:37:27,687
[man 1] I'd buy a real bed
for my little boy.

474
00:37:29,521 --> 00:37:32,937
[man 2] I'd take my dad right away
to see snow for the first time.

475
00:37:54,937 --> 00:37:57,937
[expectant music playing]

476
00:38:22,896 --> 00:38:25,896
[expectant music continues]

477
00:38:45,896 --> 00:38:47,896
[music fades]

478
00:39:18,771 --> 00:39:20,562
[man] He's making us rob Croquet?

479
00:39:35,646 --> 00:39:36,771
It's Croquet, bro!

480
00:39:37,562 --> 00:39:40,104
- Yeah, and?
- You should have said that!

481
00:39:40,187 --> 00:39:42,354
Go back to the cabin. Keep looking.

482
00:39:42,437 --> 00:39:44,062
Yeah, but this is bold! Be for real!

483
00:40:02,354 --> 00:40:05,437
It's riskier the more you drag.
Now, return to the cabin.

484
00:40:16,687 --> 00:40:19,646
You can come back in, uh, two hours?

485
00:40:19,729 --> 00:40:20,729
Okay, boss.

486
00:40:56,229 --> 00:40:59,146
We're already splitting three ways.
What do you want? More than my share?

487
00:40:59,229 --> 00:41:00,104
Screw you!

488
00:41:03,437 --> 00:41:06,312
You lied big time, bro!
You owe us a bonus!

489
00:41:06,396 --> 00:41:09,479
If you continue to stand there,
a big smack is the bonus you'll find.

490
00:41:09,562 --> 00:41:10,896
Go, now.

491
00:41:20,771 --> 00:41:22,979
That idiot Michel forget to close up?

492
00:41:26,187 --> 00:41:28,312
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

493
00:41:36,562 --> 00:41:38,062
- May I take that?
- Yes, please.

494
00:41:38,146 --> 00:41:40,146
[footsteps in background]

495
00:41:41,771 --> 00:41:43,437
[woman laughing]

496
00:41:44,271 --> 00:41:47,229
[footsteps continues]

497
00:41:52,437 --> 00:41:53,562
[glasses tinkle]

498
00:41:53,646 --> 00:41:55,687
- [Croquet] Champagne?
- Please!

499
00:42:00,521 --> 00:42:02,396
- [cork pops]
- [Croquet laughs]

500
00:42:07,146 --> 00:42:09,146
- [Croquet] To you.
- To us.

501
00:42:23,937 --> 00:42:25,896
[Croquet] Let's continue the tour.

502
00:42:25,979 --> 00:42:27,312
Oh wow!

503
00:42:28,271 --> 00:42:29,604
- You like it?
- Yes.

504
00:42:48,646 --> 00:42:50,021
[both moaning]

505
00:42:56,562 --> 00:42:58,854
[Croquet] Is the sub-prefect
in favor of the resolution?

506
00:42:58,937 --> 00:43:01,479
- [woman] It's approved, yes.
- Yeah? Mmm!

507
00:43:12,854 --> 00:43:14,854
[woman moaning]

508
00:43:47,479 --> 00:43:48,771
[softly] Oh fuck.

509
00:43:50,896 --> 00:43:52,896
[phone vibrates]

510
00:44:01,562 --> 00:44:03,979
- [woman moaning]
- [phone chimes]

511
00:44:10,854 --> 00:44:12,854
[moaning continues]

512
00:44:20,812 --> 00:44:22,854
[moaning continues]

513
00:44:43,646 --> 00:44:46,021
[Kingsley] We have to get out of here.
Hurry up.

514
00:44:53,062 --> 00:44:55,104
- [both moaning]
- [thud in background]

515
00:44:59,271 --> 00:45:00,437
[soft thud]

516
00:45:36,521 --> 00:45:37,521
[beeping]

517
00:45:37,604 --> 00:45:39,437
EMERGENCY CALL
THE POLICE RECEIVED YOUR ALERT

518
00:45:48,437 --> 00:45:50,104
[Croquet] Hello, assholes.

519
00:45:57,396 --> 00:45:59,729
- [gun fires]
- [groans] Fuck!

520
00:45:59,812 --> 00:46:02,562
- [Croquet] That's me being nice.
- That bitch shot me!

521
00:46:03,104 --> 00:46:05,562
- [indistinct police chatter on radio]
- Fuck.

522
00:46:07,146 --> 00:46:09,521
- Your destiny is on its way.
- [radio chatter continues]

523
00:46:09,604 --> 00:46:11,812
Take off your hoods
so I can see your dumb faces.

524
00:46:11,896 --> 00:46:14,646
[radio chatter continues in background]

525
00:46:16,437 --> 00:46:20,271
You'll have to shoot us all, boss,
and then explain yourself for the camera.

526
00:46:20,771 --> 00:46:24,396
"Oh, Mr. Agent, these robbers
boarded all this stuff in my boat."

527
00:46:24,896 --> 00:46:26,771
"Good thing I phoned before it left."

528
00:46:28,437 --> 00:46:30,812
"Oh really? But how's that?"

529
00:46:30,896 --> 00:46:34,104
- "Why would they do such a thing?"
- Stop your shit.

530
00:46:35,437 --> 00:46:38,937
Did you manage to film everything earlier?
Post on Insta?

531
00:46:39,021 --> 00:46:40,271
[Kingsley chuckles]

532
00:46:42,729 --> 00:46:45,271
Could you put on shorts?
I'm sick of seeing your wood!

533
00:46:47,604 --> 00:46:50,604
- [siren blaring]
- ["Chalawa" by Yaniss Odua playing]

534
00:47:02,354 --> 00:47:05,354
["Chalawa" continues playing]

535
00:47:43,104 --> 00:47:45,854
["Chalawa" continues playing]
